<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-011-150 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 485 024</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Nov 15 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>$600m DOD contract for videoconferencing awarded. (Department ofDefense)(Chesapeake andamp; Potomac Telephone)</TITLE><AUTHOR>McCormick, John.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Chesapeake and Potomac Telephone Company of Washington D.C.andO;(Contracts).andO;Topic:     Government AgencyUnited States. Department of DefenseDefense contractsVideoconferencingTelephone companies.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>$600M DOD Contract For Videoconferencing Awarded 11/15/91 WASHINGTON, DC,U.S.A., 1991 NOV 15 (NB) -- Chesapeake andamp; Potomac Telephone, a subsidiary ofBell Atlantic serving the greater Washington, DC area, will receive $600million from a 10-year Department of Defense contract which is intended tomodernize the data communications system used by the Pentagon and someintelligence agencies.andP;  The new system will reportedly provide facilities forvideo conferencing and has a capacity 50 times greater than the existingsystem.andM;The old Centrex system is being replaced with a new digital communicationssystem that will provide for e-mail and voice mail in addition to standarddata communications.andM;Rapid telecommunications services are vital for any federal agency orcontractor dealing with secure or secret projects because security rulesforbid the removal of magnetic media from secure installations, making itessential that agency departments can communicate electronically.andM;(John McCormick/19911115)</TEXT></DOC>